enhanced_by.reason: isValid(String) method checks both IPv4 and IPv6 addresses, which can be used to set up the environment for testing IPv4 addresses.
isValidInet6Address(String) method can be invoked before isValidInet4Address(String) to ensure that the input is not an IPv6 address before testing for IPv4.
The match(String) method from RegexValidator class can be used to verify the format of the input string, which is similar to the validation done in isValidInet4Address(String).
Both isValidInet4Address(String) and isValidInet6Address(String) handle similar exceptions related to invalid IP formats, making them useful for constructing assertions.
